name: Incognidium Browser Team
context: |
  The Incognidium team builds and tests a web browser engine written in Rust.
  The browser renders HTML/CSS with a custom layout engine, paints with tiny-skia,
  and runs JavaScript via the Boa engine.

  Key test sites: news.ycombinator.com, lite.cnn.com, text.npr.org,
  en.wikipedia.org, craigslist.org, google.com, github.com

  render_to_png binary: cargo run --release --bin render_to_png <url> <output.png>
  Firefox comparison: firefox --headless --screenshot <output.png> --window-size=1024,2000 <url>

  The codebase is a Rust workspace at /home/caug/npcww/incognidium with crates for
  dom, html, css, style, layout, paint, net, and shell.

forenpc: renderer
model: kimi-k2.5:cloud
provider: ollama
